This is a list of artists who have spent more than 1,000 weeks on the UK Singles Chart and UK Albums Chart combined. It uses the methodology used to compile a top 500 list in the ''British Hit Singles & Albums'' books until 2005. Any album or single must be credited to the named artist and must appear in the top 75 singles or albums chart as recorded by the Official Charts Company.<ref>cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artists/|title=View your favourite artist's chart history|accessdate=23 July 2015</ref>

Elvis Presley has the most weeks on the singles charts with 1,304 weeks for 165 singles. Cliff Richard and Rihanna are the only other artists to record over 1,000 weeks in the singles chart. Rihanna has the most weeks in the singles chart since 2000, with 1,058 between September 2005 and September 2016 &ndash; an average of over 1.8 singles per chart week during this 11-year period.

Queen (band)|Queen have the most weeks on the albums chart with over 1,500 weeks, followed by eleven other artists with more than a 1,000 weeks. David Bowie passed the 1,000-week mark following his death in January 2016, when 16 of his albums entered or re-entered the top 75.<ref>cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/albums-chart/20160115/7502/|title=Official Albums Chart Top 100 15 January 2016 - 21 January 2016|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=26 January 2016</ref>

 Artists with over 1,000 weeks combined on singles and albums charts 

Figures are as of week ending 3 January 2019.

